# Code Review Checklist

Before marking any task complete, check every item:

## Correctness

- [ ] TypeScript compiles cleanly: `npx tsc --noEmit` passes with 0 errors
- [ ] No runtime errors visible in browser console
- [ ] The change works at mobile, tablet, and desktop breakpoints
- [ ] Dynamic content (dropdowns, filters, expandable panels) opens and closes correctly

## Quality

- [ ] No `any`, `@ts-ignore`, or `as unknown as`
- [ ] No files exceed 300 lines
- [ ] No dead code, unused imports, or unused variables
- [ ] All components use named exports
- [ ] No inline `style={{ fontSize: ... }}` — use Tailwind classes
- [ ] No raw hex colors in component code (exception: NIST pillar colors via `NIST_COLORS`)

## Design

- [ ] Text meets the `text-[11px]` minimum
- [ ] Colors use design tokens from `globals.css`
- [ ] `glass-panel` is used for card surfaces
- [ ] Font weights are `extralight`, `light`, or `medium` — never `bold` or `semibold`
- [ ] Animation is subtle and serves a purpose

## UX

- [ ] Click-outside-to-close works on all dropdowns and expandable panels
- [ ] Escape key closes dropdowns
- [ ] Interactive elements have hover states
- [ ] No overlapping elements or clipped content
- [ ] Spacing is consistent with the `px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-32` section padding system

## Data

- [ ] Confidence values are 0-100 (not 0-1)
- [ ] NIST function codes use the correct 2-letter abbreviations
- [ ] Agent handles match those in `NIST_CELL_MAPPINGS`
- [ ] KPI values are computed from the data, not hardcoded

## Encoding

- [ ] No PowerShell string operations were used on files containing Unicode
- [ ] No mojibake characters visible on any page
- [ ] If files were modified via shell, encoding was verified
